import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.countplot(x='state', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airports across different states in the US?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    city_counts = data['city'].value_counts()
    ax = sns.barplot(x=city_counts.index, y=city_counts.values)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of airports across different cities in the US?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("City")
    plt.ylabel("Number of Airports")
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
from wordcloud import WordCloud

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    text = ' '.join(data['name'])
    wordcloud = WordCloud(background_color='white', width=480, height=480).generate(text)
    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport names in the US?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
